# Manual Maintenance Rule

## Trigger Conditions
Apply this rule whenever any of the following occur:
- A new skill directory is created in `.cursor/skills/`
- An existing skill in `.cursor/skills/` is significantly changed
- A new MCP server is added to `.cursor/mcp.json`
- An MCP server's status changes (e.g., from "Pending" to "Active")

## Required Updates to `ASSISTANT_MANUAL.md`

### When Adding a New Skill
1. Read the new `SKILL.md` to understand what it does.
2. Find the correct section in `ASSISTANT_MANUAL.md` ("What You Can Ask Rosy to Do"):
   - WooCommerce & Website → Commerce skills
   - Email & Marketing → Mailchimp/social skills
   - Daily Operations → system/utility skills
   - Advanced Automation → Puppeteer/script-based skills
3. Add a new entry in this format:
   ```
   **`skill-name`** *(NEW — added YYYY-MM-DD)* — Just say "[trigger phrase]"
   > I can [plain-English description of what the skill does and what Vanessa gets back].
   ```
4. Remove any `*(COMING SOON)*` placeholder for this skill if one exists.
5. Update the "Last Updated" date at the top of the file.
6. Append to `session-log.md`: `| YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM | MANUAL UPDATED | Added skill: [skill-name] |`

### When Adding a New MCP Server
1. Add a row to the MCP Integrations table under "For Advanced Reference".
2. Set Status to "Active" if credentials are live, or "Pending credentials" if not.
3. Update the "Last Updated" date.

## NEW Badge Expiry
During every **Morning Brief**, check `ASSISTANT_MANUAL.md` for any `*(NEW — added YYYY-MM-DD)*` badges.
- If the date is 7 or more days ago, remove the `*(NEW — added YYYY-MM-DD)*` text.
- Do not remove the skill entry — only the badge.
- If any badges are removed, update the "Last Updated" date.

## Writing Standards
All skill descriptions in the manual must follow these rules:
- Written in Rosy's voice, first person: "I can...", not "This skill..."
- Plain English — no technical jargon (no "MCP", "API", "JSON", "endpoint")
- End with what Vanessa receives: "...and you review the draft before anything goes live"
- Maximum 2 sentences per skill description
- COMING SOON entries are allowed for planned skills — use `*(COMING SOON)*` format

## Do Not Edit
- The "Approval System" section — only update if workflow fundamentally changes
- Security instructions — only update if credentials or process change
- The "For Advanced Reference" heading structure
